Class HashCollection<K,V>

java.lang.Object
  mai.HashCollection<K,V>

public class HashCollection<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object

This is an implementation of a Hashtable that stores more than one value per key. This is done by having every key associated with an ArrayList, and every new value being stored in the array is added to the end of the list (unless the list already contains that value)
